

Marker interface:
	
	Marker interface special kind of interface.
	Marker interface is nothing but an empty interface. 
	A interface with only body.
	Marker interface is used to group together 2 or more object.
	Marker interface is use to perform some special operation like normalization and cloning.
	
	Ex.
		Grouping.java
------------------------------------------------

		public interface Grouping{
		
		}
		
		
		Object1.java
-------------------------------------------------

		public class Object1 impliment Grouping {
		
			void print(){
			System.out.println("This is the Object1 class of group Grouping") ;
			
			}
		
		}
		
		
				
		Object2.java
-------------------------------------------------

		public class Object2 impliment Grouping {
		
			void print(){
			System.out.println("This is the Object2 class of group Grouping") ;
			
			}
		
		}
		
	Here you can see we have implimented the Grouping interface which is empty and now we can group together this two object.
		
		